Stefan Name Meaning in English

What does the name Stefan mean? What is the meaning of the name Stefan, lucky number, lucky stone, origin and religion.

From the Latin Stephanus, which is from the Greek Stephanos, a name derived from stephanos (a crown, a garland). The name is borne in the Bible by St Stephen, one of the seven chosen to assist the apostles, and the first Christian martyr. Var: Stefan, Stefen, Stefon, Stephan, Stephon, Stevan, Steven, Stevon.

Stefan Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: Crown Details: Stefan is the German form of Stephen, also used in Russia and Poland. Derived from the Greek Stephanos, meaning "crown" or "garland". Gender: For both boy and girl, unisex, transgender, neutral gender Origin: Greek Religion: Christian Suitable for: Unisex / Gender neutral Hardness: Medium hard to pronounce Uniqueness: It is a common name Short & Easy: Not very short Syllables: 6 Letters and 1 Words
